# Filmgraph Grounding Rules (Notebook-Aligned)

## Mission focus
- Prioritize shipping stable user-facing value for Filmgraph phases in `ROADMAP.md`.
- Keep Oracle, scanner, and collection flows resilient on mobile and production first.
- Never let optional enrichment block core discovery, logging, or rendering.

## Current phase context
- Current shipped baseline: Streaming Oracle MVP + UI foundation + physical-media collection surfaces.
- Active next-up work: Optional API Enrichment families behind flags (`editorial`, `visual`, `trakt`).
- Guardrail: enrichments fail-soft to TMDB/core metadata.

## High-level system logic
- Discovery/Oracle:
  - Use hybrid recommendation orchestration in `src/utils/gemini.js`.
  - Respect provider preferences from `profiles.user_providers`.
  - Provider filters and enrichments must degrade gracefully.
- Physical media:
  - UPC scan and lookup starts in `src/components/LogMovieModal.jsx`.
  - UPC lookup logic lives in `src/api/upc.js`.
  - Server-side UPC proxy endpoint is `api/upc-lookup.js`.
  - Ownership source-of-truth is `movie_logs.source_upc`.
- Collection views:
  - Library `Collection` shelf is filtered by `source_upc IS NOT NULL`.
  - Profile and movie detail surfaces should reuse this ownership signal.

## Implementation constraints
- Keep existing stack conventions (React + Vite + custom CSS + Supabase).
- Reuse existing API modules; avoid scattering raw fetches in UI components.
- Prefer minimal, low-risk changes over broad rewrites.
- Keep mobile compatibility first (camera, touch targets, loading/perf).

## Definition of done for phase work
- User-visible behavior works on live deployment.
- Lints clean for touched files and production build passes.
- `CHANGELOG.md` and relevant roadmap status are updated when features ship.

## Documentation export protocol
- After each major feature/phase:
  - produce a concise implementation summary (what/where/why/fallbacks/tests),
  - include key paths touched,
  - include known risks + next actions.
